## Phase 1 — Deterministic Slicer

**New file: `backend/utils/ewa_slicer.py`**

**Step 1.1 — `slice_chapters(markdown: str) -> dict[int, ChapterData]`**
- Walk lines; detect chapter boundary: line matches `^# (\d+)\s+` (e.g., `# 11 Security`)
- For each chapter, collect lines until the next `# N` boundary
- Within a chapter's lines, detect `^## (\d+\.\d+)` subsections
- Return `dict` keyed by chapter number; value is a `ChapterData` dataclass:
  ```python
  @dataclass
  class ChapterData:
      number: int
      title: str
      raw_content: str
      subsections: list[tuple[str, str]]  # (title, content)
  ```
- Preamble (lines before `# 1`) is stored under key `0` (cover page, handled by dispatcher as skip)

**Step 1.2 — `truncate_large_chapter(chapter: ChapterData, char_limit: int = 8000) -> ChapterData`**
- If `len(chapter.raw_content) > char_limit`:
  - Count subsections: `n_subs = len(chapter.subsections)`
  - Extract overview: lines up to the first `##` heading (up to `char_limit`)
  - Replace `raw_content` with overview + `"\n\n[TRUNCATED: {n_subs} subsections found. Refer to original report for full details.]"`
  - Sets flag in subsections list as `[("__truncated__", f"{n_subs} subsections")]`
- Call this on ch19 automatically (ch19 has ~4,000 lines / ~200k chars)

**Verify Phase 1:**
- Test with SHP_20474620_850648038_2026-03-02_R_EWA.md
- Assert `len(chapters) == 23`
- Assert `chapters[19].subsections[0][0] == "__truncated__"` (ch19 was truncated)
- Assert `chapters[11].title == "Security"` (exact match)

