## Phase 4 — Excel Builder

**Modify: excel_utils.py**

**Step 4.1 — Add `build_workbook(domain_results, supplemental_findings, system_metadata) -> bytes`**

Does NOT touch the existing `json_to_excel()` function.

**Tab 1 — Executive Summary**
- System metadata header (system ID, report date — passed in `system_metadata`)
- Domain RAG status matrix: one row per domain, column = `findings_count | params_count | worst_rag | deep_thinker_count`
- Top risks table: 5 most severe findings across all domains (sort by `rag_status=red` first, then by finding count)
- Supplemental highlights: top 3 Deep Thinker findings

**Tabs 2–7 — Domain tabs** (Security, Database, Performance, Basis, Business, Lifecycle)

Each tab has 4 sections, written top-to-bottom on the same sheet with section header rows:
- **Section A: Findings** — `finding_id | source_chapter | title | rag_status | description | impact`
- **Section B: Parameters** — `param_name | current_value | recommended_value | rag_status | action | source_chapter`
- **Section C: Deep Thinker Supplements** — supplemental_findings filtered to this domain
- **Section D: Abstentions** — `chapter | reason` (all abstention entries from the domain result)

Reuse existing SAP color palette, `_apply_header_style()`, `_apply_data_style()`, `_auto_fit_columns()` from `excel_utils.py`.

